caption: We came here on a recommendation from the Evan Williams Bourbon Experience staff for a quick bite before our tour. It was one of the only places open during our stay in Louisville as nearly all restaurants were still closed due to COVID-19.  They have numerous options from deli style sandwiches, salads, and soups to an all scratch made, home style, hot entree and 2 sides meal.  I opted for the fried chicken and 2 sides. It was one of the best homemade Southern meals I have had in ages. And the service was truly hospitable.
Love the place and guys and girls who work here

Cravings catered our wedding reception, and our guests are still raving about their meal! Dinner was absolutely delicious, decadent. The quality of the food, the beautiful presentation, and the service is unmatched. Chuck, Brian, and the team helped us every step of the way- from guiding us through our menu selection to helping us add extra health and safety precautions. It was not easy to get married in 2020, but Chuck was so reassuring and patient. They think of everything. The chef even had the foresight to donate the leftover food from our reception to a local mission. We were so touched. The personal treatment you will get from this family-owned business removes a lot of stress from the event-planning process. We felt completely taken care of, we know our guests did too. And did I mention how absolutely amazing the food was?!

Great option for lunch in the business district. It's located in the lower level of the PNC building. There is also plenty of seating available. They have a cafeteria style setup where you can choose an entree and sides (varies daily), full salad bar, grill-to-order, deli, soup bar and a large drinks station. They have plenty of healthy options also. There's not much that they don't have here. It's not "fancy" food, just good down-to-earth comfort food at a great price. You will never leave hungry. Staff is always friendly and helpful.

The staff is extremely friendly (except for one manager guy who's always stressed)...also the place is super convenient for those working nearby. That's good enough for 2 stars. That said, the food is terrible unless you want to re-live your high school cafeteria days. Avoid the hot bar...I've tried about everything they serve and always end up sick to my stomach. You might say, "then why do you go back?", and my answer is convenience and desperation. If you must, your best options are their salad bar or a custom deli sandwich. Try a food truck instead.
